  "text": "The Envoy hot restart mechanism is implemented across 14 C++ source files in envoyproxy/envoy, enabling graceful server updates with zero connection loss. The architecture consists of several interconnected components:\n\n**Core Interface and Implementation:**\n- `envoy/server/hot_restart.h` defines the HotRestart interface, specifying the contract for hot restart operations including drainParentListeners(), duplicateParentListenSocket(), and mergeParentStatsIfAny().\n- `source/server/hot_restart_impl.h` and `hot_restart_impl.cc` provide the main implementation, managing shared memory attachment via attachSharedMemory() and coordinating parent/child process interactions.\n- `source/server/hot_restart_nop_impl.h` provides a no-op implementation for systems where hot restart is disabled.\n\n**Protocol and Communication:**\n- `source/server/hot_restart.proto` defines the HotRestartMessage protocol with request/reply types for PassListenSocket, ShutdownAdmin, Stats, DrainListeners, and Terminate operations.\n- `source/server/hot_restarting_base.h` and `hot_restarting_base.cc` contain the RpcStream class, implementing the custom RPC protocol over Unix domain sockets with fd passing via CMSG control messages.\n\n**Parent Process Implementation:**\n- `source/server/hot_restarting_parent.h` and `hot_restarting_parent.cc` handle the parent process side, binding to Unix domain sockets, receiving child requests, and responding with socket file descriptors (via sendmsg/recvmsg with SCM_RIGHTS).\n- The Internal class within HotRestartingParent handles getListenSocketsForChild() for socket passing, drainListeners() for graceful shutdown, and exportStatsToChild() for stats merging.\n\n**Child Process Implementation:**\n- `source/server/hot_restarting_child.h` and `hot_restarting_child.cc` implement the child process side, issuing requests to the parent via duplicateParentListenSocket(), sending drain/terminate signals, and managing UDP forwarding for QUIC packets.\n- The UdpForwardingContext tracks registered UDP listeners by address for forwarding packets from the draining parent.\n\n**System Call Abstraction:**\n- `envoy/api/os_sys_calls_hot_restart.h` defines the HotRestartOsSysCalls interface for shared memory operations.\n- `source/common/api/posix/os_sys_calls_impl_hot_restart.h` and `hot_restart_impl_hot_restart.cc` provide POSIX implementations of shmOpen() and shmUnlink() for managing /dev/shm segments.\n\n**Key Mechanisms:**\n1. **Shared Memory:** attachSharedMemory() creates or attaches to a shared memory segment containing SharedMemory struct with version compatibility checks, process-shared pthread mutexes, and initialization flags.\n2. **Domain Socket Communication:** RpcStream establishes AF_UNIX SOCK_DGRAM sockets for parent-child IPC, with socket names incorporating base_id, role (parent/child), and restart epoch.\n3. **File Descriptor Passing:** Socket file descriptors are passed via control messages (CMSG_SPACE/CMSG_DATA with SOL_SOCKET/SCM_RIGHTS) in sendmsg/recvmsg calls.\n4. **Drain Sequence:** drainListeners() initiates graceful shutdown in parent, while child tracks parent_drained_ status before fully taking over.\n5. **Child Readiness:** Child process initialization via initialize() includes parent connection validation (abortDueToFailedParentConnection) and UDP forwarding socket event registration.\n6. **Stats Merging:** mergeParentStatsIfAny() retrieves counters, gauges, and dynamic stat information from parent via the Stats protobuf message.\n7. **UDP Forwarding:** Separate RPC stream (udp_forwarding_rpc_stream_) handles QUIC packet forwarding during drain to prevent loss."
}
